node.title: Search resumes for swimmer missing at Auckland beach
node.description: The search for a missing swimmer at Auckland's Karioitahi Beach has been scaled down during high tide.
node.content:
["The search for a missing swimmer at Auckland's Karioitahi Beach has been scaled down during high tide.", "", "
File pic Photo: Auckland Council
", "Police say they were notified at 8.15pm yesterday that a person was missing in the water at the west coast beach.", "They say aerial and water searches took place last night but the person has not been found.", "Surf Life Saving New Zealand's Dan Short said the search for the swimmer, a middle aged male, went for an hour last night before it got too dark to continue.", "He said lifeguards, the eagle helicopter and the Coastguard air patrol did a shoreline sweep and search of the inshore area this morning in an attempt to locate the man.", "There have been at least 30 water-related deaths since the beginning of December."]
